## Initializing development environment

The agent environment setup script installs miniforge for conda and tox for unit tests. The following environment variable (and secrets) are already configured:

- `GITHUB_PAT`: The github personal access token (PAT) to use with private repositories
- `GITHUB_USERNAME`: The github username to use for authentication with the PAT

The setup script also installs tox and caches all of the  and conda environments.

For a development environment, activate the `{{ package_name }}-py312-dev-runner` conda environment.

```bash
conda activate {{ package_name }}-py312-dev-runner
```

## The `{{ package_name }}` python package

This package contains the `runner` extras that are specified in `pyproject.toml`. Sub-modules that require extras reside in a `runner/` subdirectory.

## Snakemake workflows

Many of the snakemake rules require specialized conda environments as specified by the `conda:` directive that are available (after environment initialization) in the `workflow/envs/localized` directory.

## Documentation

Tox is used to run all the tests. The environment initialization already installed all the packages. The rule integration tests depend on snakemake which requires an internet connection to create conda environments, so skip those. To speed things up, run tox in parallel and skip the rule integration environments:

```bash
tox run-parallel --parallel auto --parallel-no-spinner --skip-pkg-install --skip-env='py.*-workflow-rules'
```

Parallel execution is safe because each tox environment writes its own files in `.cover/` and `.junit/`. Directory creation uses `mkdir -p`, so races are avoided. If any environment needs exclusive access to a resource, add a check in its `commands_pre` section and raise an error.

## Set-up script

```bash
# Install miniforge
wget -O "${HOME}/Miniforge3.sh" "https://github.com/conda-forge/miniforge/releases/latest/download/Miniforge3-$(uname)-$(uname -m).sh"
bash "${HOME}/Miniforge3.sh" -b -p "${HOME}/conda"
${HOME}/conda/bin/conda init
source "${HOME}/conda/etc/profile.d/conda.sh"
conda activate

# Install snakemake
conda env update --quiet \
  --name "{{ package_name }}_py312_workflow" \
  --file "workflow/envs/{{ package_name }}-py312-workflow.yaml"
conda activate {{ package_name }}_py312_workflow

# Configure git to use token via credential helper
git config --global credential.helper 'store --file ~/.git-credentials'
echo "https://$GITHUB_USERNAME:$GITHUB_PAT@github.com" > ~/.git-credentials

# Load the submodules
git submodule update --init --recursive

# Write conda dev environments yaml files
snakemake conda_localize
snakemake --conda-create-envs-only

# Install uv and tox
pipx install uv
uv tool install tox --with tox-uv

# Cache Tox environment with access to conda
tox run --recreate --notest --skip-missing-interpreters false
```
